Let me analyze the target image and block dictionary to provide a detailed solution:

Target Image Analysis:
- Total Blocks: 8 blocks
- Colors: Blue, Yellow, Orange/Red, Green
- Layers: 2-3 layers in height
- Complex spatial arrangement with arched and cylindrical elements

Block Selection from Dictionary:
1. Red Arch Block (Index 1): Base layer, curved arch
2. Red Vertical Block (Index 2): Vertical block on arch
3. Blue Cube (Index 3): Top left small blue cube
4. Green Rectangular Block (Index 4): Right side green block
5. Yellow Rectangular Blocks (Indices 6, 7, 12, 13): Various yellow blocks
6. Orange/Red Cylindrical Blocks (Indices 8, 9): Orange/red cylindrical blocks
7. Orange Triangular Block (Index 16): Triangular orange block at top right

Assembly Instructions:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 1 (Red Arch)
    Step2: Move block with index 2 (Red Vertical Block) on top of Arch
    Step3: Move block with index 6 (Yellow Rectangular Block) next to Red Vertical Block
    Step4: Move block with index 9 (Orange Cylindrical Block) beside previous blocks
    Step5: Move block with index 7 (Yellow Vertical Block) on the right side
    Step6: Move block with index 16 (Orange Triangular Block) on top of Yellow Vertical Block
    Step7: Move block with index 3 (Blue Cube) on top of left side blocks
    Step8: Move block with index 4 (Green Rectangular Block) on right side
}
